processedText:
Cri. Bail Appl. No. 33/2019 ( CNR No. : MHPU01­000118­2019 ) Rushikesh Yadav­Patil Vs. State of Maharashtra 
---header-ends---
ORDER BELOW EXH. 1 1] This is an application by Rushikesh Pradip Yadav­Patil for regular bail under Section 439 of Code of Criminal Procedure in respect of Crime No. 667/2018 registered under Section 306 of Indian Penal Code at Police Station, Chaturshrungi, Pune. 
---background-ends---
2] The crime has been registered on report of Sangita Pavase who is mother of victim girl Tejal. She alleged that, her daughter Tejal got acquainted with Applicant through social media. She used to chat with Applicant. But Applicant avoided her and denied for love affair. Therefore, due to frustration her daughter committed suicide by hanging herself on 17/12/2018. Hence, she lodged the report. 
---argument-ends---
3] Applicant submits that, he is resident of Sangli. The incident had taken place at Pune. He never met victim Tejal. He was not present at the spot. Absolutely there was no inducement to Tejal by Applicant. Moreover, police arrested him on suspicion on 29/12/2018. Practically investigation is over. Therefore, he prays for grant of bail. 
---argument-ends---
4] Learned APP Mr. Satpute appeared for Respondent/State and filed report of investigation officer. He submits that, due to denial of Applicant for love affair and friendship, victim has committed suicide. Investigation is in progress. Therefore, the application may be rejected. 
---argument-ends---
5] Heard the learned Adv. A. P. Malviya for Applicant and the learned APP Mr. Satpute for Respondent/State. Perused the Papers. 
---argument-ends---
6] Prima facie, Applicant is resident of Sangli. Incident had taken place at Pune. The allegations are to the extent that, Applicant avoided chatting with victim due to his business work. Prima facie, Applicant not seen to be intended that, victim to commit suicide. Investigation with the Applicant is over. Further detention of the Applicant is not necessary. Hence, I prefer to pass following Order. 
---argument-ends---
ORDER 1] The application is allowed. 2] The applicant, namely, Rushikesh Pradip Yadav­Patil be released on bail on executing P.R. bond of Rs. 15,000/­ (Rupees Fifteen Thousand Only) with solvent surety of the like amount in Crime No. 667/2018 registered under Section 306 of Indian Penal Code at Police Station, Chaturshrungi, Pune on the following terms and conditions. [i] Applicant to co­operate investigation machinery fully. ..2.. [ii] Applicant should not contact witnesses and should not tamper the evidence in the matter. [iii] Applicant to provide proof of his permanent address and contact details to the investigation officer. [iv] Applicant should not indulge into any crime. [v] Applicant should not change his address and contact details without intimation to the court. 3] Bail before the concern Court of Magistrate. 4] Intimate to the concern Police Station accordingly. 
---order-ends---
